title: Prep soccer roundup: Apollo advances to 8A title match
text:

FERGUS FALLS — Abdinajib Yussuf scored off of an assist from Logan Lommel with 6:08 left in overtime to give second-seeded St. Cloud Apollo at 3-2 win over top-seeded West Ottertail United on Tuesday in the Section 8A boys soccer semifinals. 
Apollo (16-3) advances to play Sartell (13-2-4) in the Section 8A title game at 6 p.m. Thursday at St. Cloud State’s Husky Stadium. The Eagles are the defending state champions. 
Apollo’s Khadar Mohamed tied the game up on a free kick with 43 seconds left in regulation to force overtime. 
Graham Virtue scored the other goal for the Eagles. Danny Wieber had seven saves in goal to get the win. 
SARTELL 4, ALEXANDRIA 1 
SARTELL — Junior Traivis Forst scored two goals to lead the Sabres in their win over Alexandria on Tuesday. 
Senior Matthew Michaud recorded his first career goal for the Sabres (13-2-4). Also scoring a goal for Sartell was junior Riley Sanderson. 
Senior Colin Johnson made three saves in the win. 
The Sabres advance to face St. Cloud Apollo at 6 p.m. Thursday at St. Cloud State in the section final. 
GIRLS 
Section 8A 
SARTELL 1, ALEXANDRIA 0 
ALEXANDRIA — Claire Minnerath scored with 13 seconds left to lift second-seeded Sartell past top-seeded Alexandria in the Section 8A playoffs. 
After a near Alexandria goal, Sartell cleared the ball back to midfield until Minnerath’s shot from 30 yards out deflected off of a Cardinals defender to score the game-winning goal. 
Sarah Higgins had seven saves in goal to get the win for Sartell (13-4-2). 
The Sabres play St. Cloud Apollo in the Section 8A championship game at 8 p.m. Thursday at St. Cloud State’s Husky Stadium. 
ST. CLOUD APOLLO 1, LITTLE FALLS 0 
LITTLE FALLS — Fourth-seeded St. Cloud Apollo edged past No. 3 Little Falls in the Section 8-2A semifinal. 
The Eagles (8-8-1) will face No. 2 Sartell (13-4-2) in the Section 8-2A championship at 8 p.m. Thursday at St. Cloud State’s Husky Stadium.
